18 MONTHS!

when I began my mission, I became sister hardy. God took lexie for a little while and and promised her that while I was on His errand, He would take care of her.

sister hardy has learned a whole lot out there. 

I have learned that the scriptures truly change lives and that they contain an abundance of wisdom. 

I have learned the importance of the book of mormon and the precious truths we are SO lucky to have. 

I have learned the power of prayer and how to make it a relationship instead of a routine. 

I have come to love the temple and solace and peace that comes from attending.

I have come to love the act performed by Christ in the garden of gethsemane. I have learned how real the atonement is. 
 
I have come to know the power of a simple testimony.

and most importantly,

I have learned how to seek Jesus continually. 

I have taken these things and smeared them into my heart forever !!!

I'm overjoyed to be home and reunited with my family and friends! my homecoming will be on march 12th at 10:30am in highland, UT! message me for the address! 🤎
philly will always have my heart !

sometimes we put our faith into the fact that our sick grandparent is going to be healed.

or we put our faith in the fact that we are going to get our dream job.

that we are going to pass our exam.

that we are going to be healed from mental illness.

that we are going to get over this break up. 

that we are going to overcome addiction.

that we are going to mend a broken friendship. 

but honestly 

none of this can happen or will happen,

if we have faith in the outcome. 

we need to have faith in Jesus Christ first. 

when we have faith in Jesus, the change will follow.

the healing.

the miracle.

the grace. 

the freedom. 

the joy. 

why? 

because of the sacrifice that that Heavenly Father made for His children. 

that His only beloved Son,

came so we could have faith in someone bigger than ourselves. 

that a wish could turn into a miracle, 

if we have faith in Christ.

I've anticipated this day for about two years. 

my first wedding back as a returned missionary! 

I thought about it over the past two years, what it was going to feel like coming full circle. 

the whole wedding I kept thinking about how Jesus would love this. 

the smiles 

the laughter

the tears

the warm spring weather 

the tulips (!)

the yummy food 

the father daughter dance 

the groomsman wiping his tears with a pink napkin because his best friend found his forever lover. 

I am overwhelmed with gratitude

and could have never seen it on this fashion 

the abundance of blessings my mission would pull into all aspects of my life. 

you hear returned missionaries say it all the time, but I wanted a turn to say it too 

because it's true! 

I will never take for granted this special job where love spills over all day. 🫶🏼

we've got some new faces around here 🕊️ 

hi i am lexie! 

one of my favorite sayings in life is "if you love what you do, you will never work a day in your life." 

nothing resonates more! 

i am 21 and have been doing photography since I was 17. it is my world! you lovely humans are my world! 

i love capturing the hand squeezes, the eye smiles and most of all the relationships. 

where the love began, where the love is at and what the love will flourish to become. 

now a little bit about me! 

i grew up in northern colorado and moved to utah one week after graduating high school. 

i dropped out of college at 18 to pursue photo full time.

philadelphia had a place in my heart🫶🏼 i spent 18 months teaching people about jesus there!

i love fashion, gluten free food, my jeep, lany, and most of all- my friends and family. 

thanks for being here. supporting something i love so much. 

cheers to love, growth, christ and happiness this year! 

@lexie.hardy x @rileykathleenphotography (she's amazing!!!!!)

and read them without looking at each other.

this was so beautiful to me.

they were reminded of the inter beauty of themselves 

why they are so deeply appreciated by one another 

why their souls intertwine 

why they are choosing each other-

all day and everyday.
